00:35:59.373 --> 00:36:02.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎What a blessing it is to have true friends

00:36:02.677 --> 00:36:06.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎around us in the Christian congregation!

00:36:06.113 --> 00:36:08.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But at times,

00:36:08.115 --> 00:36:11.452 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎our imperfection may create roadblocks

00:36:11.452 --> 00:36:14.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎between us and our dear friends,

00:36:14.322 --> 00:36:16.757 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and we may start developing

00:36:16.757 --> 00:36:19.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎negative feelings about them. 

00:36:19.493 --> 00:36:22.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎In this Bethel morning worship,

00:36:22.330 --> 00:36:26.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎pay attention to how Brother Geoffrey Jackson 
‎of the Governing Body

00:36:26.868 --> 00:36:30.037 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎helps us deal with such thinking.

00:36:30.471 --> 00:36:33.007 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, perhaps we could take our Bibles 

00:36:33.007 --> 00:36:37.044 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
‎and turn to Colossians 3:​13. 

00:36:37.044 --> 00:36:39.513 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
‎And let’s analyze this verse together 

00:36:39.513 --> 00:36:43.584 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
‎and see what it is that Jehovah expects of us.

00:36:43.584 --> 00:36:46.420 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So in Colossians 3:​13,

00:36:46.420 --> 00:36:49.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎it says: 
‎“Continue putting up with one another

00:36:49.657 --> 00:36:52.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“and forgiving one another freely

00:36:52.026 --> 00:36:55.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“even if anyone has a cause 
‎for complaint against another.

00:36:55.897 --> 00:36:58.833 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Just as Jehovah freely forgave you,

00:36:58.833 --> 00:37:01.435 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎you must also do the same.”

00:37:01.435 --> 00:37:03.437 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, certainly this verse

00:37:03.437 --> 00:37:06.340 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎gives us plenty of food for thought
‎​—doesn’t it?​—

00:37:06.340 --> 00:37:10.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎areas in which, perhaps, 
‎we can work on and improve in.

00:37:10.378 --> 00:37:12.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But what two things stand out

00:37:12.780 --> 00:37:15.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎as being required of us?

00:37:15.049 --> 00:37:17.585 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, looking back, 
‎you notice the first one,

00:37:17.585 --> 00:37:20.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“continue putting up with one another,”

00:37:20.321 --> 00:37:22.723 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and then the second point,

00:37:22.723 --> 00:37:25.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“forgiving one another freely.”

00:37:25.760 --> 00:37:28.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, let’s look at that first expression:

00:37:28.162 --> 00:37:30.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Continue putting up with one another.”

00:37:30.765 --> 00:37:34.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, what’s the difference 
‎between these two expressions?

00:37:34.268 --> 00:37:37.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, we’re told that this first expression

00:37:37.171 --> 00:37:41.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎doesn’t refer to serious sins 
‎but perhaps talks about things

00:37:41.475 --> 00:37:44.679 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that are irritating, annoying,

00:37:44.679 --> 00:37:47.048 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎things that we may not necessarily

00:37:47.048 --> 00:37:49.417 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎have a cause for complaint concerning,

00:37:49.417 --> 00:37:52.820 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but they still get us very upset anyway

00:37:52.820 --> 00:37:55.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎​—these minor things.

00:37:55.523 --> 00:37:57.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎What are some of the things that annoy you?

00:37:57.658 --> 00:38:00.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Let’s be honest.

00:38:00.394 --> 00:38:05.132 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Are you annoyed when someone is always late?

00:38:05.132 --> 00:38:09.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Are you annoyed when they’re always early?

00:38:09.537 --> 00:38:13.474 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Are you annoyed when someone is outspoken?

00:38:13.474 --> 00:38:17.211 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Does it annoy you when someone is too quiet?

00:38:17.211 --> 00:38:19.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s amazing​
‎—isn’t it?​—

00:38:19.213 --> 00:38:21.282 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎what the things that annoy us are.

00:38:21.282 --> 00:38:25.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I remember back in the ’70’s, 
‎Brother Knorr gave an outstanding talk

00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:30.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎where he alluded to the fact 
‎that maybe there’s a sister in the congregation,

00:38:30.224 --> 00:38:33.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and she’s hearing 
‎this other sister, new in the truth,

00:38:33.260 --> 00:38:35.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎answering up time after time,

00:38:35.329 --> 00:38:37.331 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and in her heart, she’s thinking,

00:38:37.331 --> 00:38:40.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎‘Why doesn’t she just keep quiet?’ 

00:38:40.434 --> 00:38:43.637 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, maybe we’ve all 
‎experienced those feelings.

00:38:43.637 --> 00:38:47.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And if we’re judged on them,
‎perhaps we’ll agree: 

00:38:47.441 --> 00:38:50.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎‘Well, it’s not justified; 
‎I don’t really have a cause,

00:38:50.311 --> 00:38:53.080 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but it still irritates me.’

00:38:53.080 --> 00:38:55.249 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s true—isn’t it?​—
‎the expression 

00:38:55.249 --> 00:38:59.487 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Sometimes it’s not the mountains
‎ahead of us that cause problems, 

00:38:59.487 --> 00:39:01.589 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎it’s the pebble in the shoe.”

00:39:01.589 --> 00:39:04.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And it’s sometimes the small things

00:39:04.125 --> 00:39:06.427 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that irritate us the most.

00:39:06.427 --> 00:39:08.429 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I remember when I was serving

00:39:08.429 --> 00:39:11.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎in Western Samoa 
‎many years ago at the branch,

00:39:11.599 --> 00:39:15.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎we had quite a number of brothers 
‎from overseas working on construction.

00:39:15.603 --> 00:39:19.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And there was one brother who had
‎the habit of first thing in the morning

00:39:19.440 --> 00:39:22.443 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎as he arrived before breakfast,

00:39:22.443 --> 00:39:26.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎saying, “Good morning!” to everyone.

00:39:26.914 --> 00:39:30.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Some found that annoying.

00:39:30.217 --> 00:39:32.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Maybe you can relate to that.

00:39:32.753 --> 00:39:35.956 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And, no doubt, you feel 
‎very happy when you read the scripture

00:39:35.956 --> 00:39:39.660 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎at Proverbs 27:14, 
‎where it says in one translation:

00:39:39.660 --> 00:39:42.963 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎‘A loud and cheerful greeting
‎early in the morning 

00:39:42.963 --> 00:39:45.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎is taken as a curse.’

00:39:45.966 --> 00:39:49.070 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎You may be thinking, ‘Amen to that.’

00:39:49.070 --> 00:39:52.740 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And that brother ceased his habit
‎after he read that scripture​

00:39:52.740 --> 00:39:54.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—or at least it was read to him.

00:39:56.410 --> 00:39:59.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But we may not always be able
‎to find a scripture 

00:39:59.680 --> 00:40:03.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that backs up this irritation that we feel.

00:40:03.184 --> 00:40:04.685 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So, what do we do?

00:40:04.685 --> 00:40:06.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, what does it say?

00:40:06.353 --> 00:40:09.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Continue putting up with one another.”

00:40:09.523 --> 00:40:13.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Continue”​—it’s something 
‎that we just have to keep on doing.

00:40:13.828 --> 00:40:17.098 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Now, that brings us 
‎to the second part of our verse,

00:40:17.098 --> 00:40:20.401 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“forgiving one another freely.”

00:40:20.401 --> 00:40:24.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s interesting, when we look 
‎at other translations of this verse,

00:40:24.772 --> 00:40:27.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎most follow the King James Version

00:40:27.608 --> 00:40:30.211 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and just say “forgive.”

00:40:30.211 --> 00:40:34.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The New World Translation says ‘forgive freely.’

00:40:34.548 --> 00:40:37.084 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The reason is that this isn’t your normal

00:40:37.084 --> 00:40:39.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Greek word for “forgiveness.”

00:40:39.720 --> 00:40:42.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It denotes generosity,

00:40:42.823 --> 00:40:46.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎a willingness to go beyond what’s required.

00:40:46.594 --> 00:40:51.198 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s interesting 
‎that The Watchtower even back in 1882

00:40:51.198 --> 00:40:55.269 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎was using that expression, 
‎to ‘forgive one another freely,’

00:40:55.269 --> 00:40:58.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎well before the time 
‎of the New World Translation.

00:40:58.739 --> 00:41:01.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So this gives us something to think about

00:41:01.175 --> 00:41:04.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎because it’s not just a matter of forgiving,

00:41:04.178 --> 00:41:07.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but we need to be generous about forgiving.

00:41:07.381 --> 00:41:12.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We have to be willing to,  
‎as it were, bestow a pardon

00:41:12.052 --> 00:41:16.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎on someone 
‎who really doesn’t deserve that pardon.

00:41:16.123 --> 00:41:18.425 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Now, why should we be interested

00:41:18.425 --> 00:41:21.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎in developing 
‎and working on these two aspects:

00:41:21.729 --> 00:41:25.766 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“putting up with one another”
‎and ‘forgiving freely’? 

00:41:25.766 --> 00:41:29.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, we’ve heard 
‎the reasons many times before, haven’t we?

00:41:29.703 --> 00:41:33.107 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The first one, of course, 
‎is that Jehovah has forgiven us.

00:41:33.107 --> 00:41:35.709 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎If we turn back just one chapter,

00:41:35.709 --> 00:41:39.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎chapter 2 of Colossians and verse 13,

00:41:39.647 --> 00:41:42.349 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎this point is highlighted for us.

00:41:42.349 --> 00:41:45.452 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It says in chapter 2, verse 13:

00:41:45.452 --> 00:41:48.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Furthermore, though you 
‎were dead in your trespasses

00:41:48.689 --> 00:41:51.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“and in the uncircumcised state of your flesh,

00:41:51.258 --> 00:41:54.195 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“God made you alive together with him.

00:41:54.195 --> 00:41:59.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“He kindly forgave us

00:41:59.200 --> 00:42:01.468 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎all our trespasses.”

00:42:01.468 --> 00:42:04.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So this is the model 
‎that Jehovah has given us.

00:42:04.772 --> 00:42:09.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s true, 
‎we sometimes can find some reason

00:42:09.176 --> 00:42:12.179 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎why we feel 
‎we don’t have to forgive someone else.

00:42:12.179 --> 00:42:15.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But remember the illustration Jesus gave

00:42:15.182 --> 00:42:17.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎of the slave who had the huge debt.

00:42:17.785 --> 00:42:20.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎If you calculated it in denarius,

00:42:20.154 --> 00:42:24.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎there were 60 million denarii that he owed;

00:42:24.258 --> 00:42:26.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎he was forgiven that.

00:42:26.260 --> 00:42:28.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Then he went after the other man

00:42:28.495 --> 00:42:30.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎who owed him just a small amount.

00:42:30.731 --> 00:42:33.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But have you ever thought 
‎that if you asked that slave,

00:42:33.267 --> 00:42:35.269 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎maybe he would say: “Well, it’s true.

00:42:35.269 --> 00:42:39.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“I really appreciate having everything forgiven,
‎but I still don’t have any money. 

00:42:39.807 --> 00:42:42.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“I need some money, 
‎so that’s why I wanted to get

00:42:42.409 --> 00:42:45.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the other slave to give me the money.”

00:42:45.279 --> 00:42:47.348 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, there’s always a reason
‎​—isn’t there?​—

00:42:47.348 --> 00:42:49.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎⁠even if it’s a distorted reason

00:42:49.416 --> 00:42:52.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎as to why we don’t follow Jehovah’s example.

00:42:52.720 --> 00:42:57.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But looking back at Colossians 3:​13,
‎what does it say? 

00:42:57.157 --> 00:43:01.862 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“If anyone has a cause 
‎for complaint against another.”

00:43:01.862 --> 00:43:04.932 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So that gives us a good idea, doesn’t it?

00:43:04.932 --> 00:43:07.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The second reason, of course, is that

00:43:07.434 --> 00:43:10.638 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎we do need others to forgive us.

00:43:10.638 --> 00:43:14.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The very things that annoy us

00:43:14.642 --> 00:43:18.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and irritate us in others are sometimes

00:43:18.045 --> 00:43:20.281 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the same things that we do to others.

00:43:20.281 --> 00:43:22.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Have you ever noticed that?

00:43:22.116 --> 00:43:24.752 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And how annoying it is 
‎when someone points that out to you:

00:43:24.752 --> 00:43:26.787 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“You’re annoyed with that person? 

00:43:26.787 --> 00:43:29.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Don’t you realize what you do?”

00:43:29.390 --> 00:43:32.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, that’s something good for us to remember​
‎—isn’t it?​—

00:43:32.226 --> 00:43:35.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the fact that we do need 
‎to have others forgive us.

00:43:35.296 --> 00:43:37.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And then another reason

00:43:37.298 --> 00:43:41.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎is that it maintains the peace 
‎within the Christian congregation.

00:43:41.702 --> 00:43:43.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The Watchtower made a comment on this.

00:43:43.937 --> 00:43:48.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It said that in countries 
‎where our work is restricted or under ban,

00:43:48.876 --> 00:43:53.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎many of our brothers 
‎have to meet together in smaller groups.

00:43:53.213 --> 00:43:55.616 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And when you do that, you get to know

00:43:55.616 --> 00:43:58.752 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎everyone’s weaknesses and idiosyncrasies.

00:43:58.752 --> 00:44:01.955 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It’s so much easier to be annoyed by others

00:44:01.955 --> 00:44:05.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎when you’re dealing 
‎with small groups of persons.

00:44:05.025 --> 00:44:07.328 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The Watchtower then made the comment

00:44:07.328 --> 00:44:09.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎what good training it is for us now

00:44:09.797 --> 00:44:12.099 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎to learn how to put up with one another

00:44:12.099 --> 00:44:14.168 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎when we’re in larger groups,

00:44:14.168 --> 00:44:18.439 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎because later we may need 
‎to worship Jehovah in smaller groups.

00:44:18.439 --> 00:44:23.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So it’s good training for us 
‎as we keep peace in the congregation.

00:44:23.243 --> 00:44:24.745 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And what can help us?

00:44:24.745 --> 00:44:28.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Well, there are many different things
‎that can help us in this regard. 

00:44:28.115 --> 00:44:30.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The one point in the marginal reference

00:44:30.551 --> 00:44:33.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎you see there is at 1 Peter 4:​8,

00:44:33.854 --> 00:44:35.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and that’s where it tells us we need

00:44:35.856 --> 00:44:39.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎to “have intense love for one another”​

00:44:39.593 --> 00:44:42.196 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—not just love but “intense love.”

00:44:42.196 --> 00:44:45.432 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And this word “intense” means “full strength.”

00:44:45.432 --> 00:44:49.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Literally, it means “to stretch out our love.”

00:44:49.236 --> 00:44:54.274 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So as we come across these things
‎that irritate us, annoy us, in life 

00:44:54.274 --> 00:44:58.679 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎or if we come across persons 
‎who actually do sin against us,

00:44:58.679 --> 00:45:00.714 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎what should we keep in mind?

00:45:00.714 --> 00:45:03.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“Continue putting up with one another.”

00:45:03.784 --> 00:45:07.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎‘Continue freely forgiving one another.’

00:45:07.821 --> 00:45:12.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎That sound advice 
‎also applies strongly in marriage,

00:45:12.259 --> 00:45:16.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎when two people decide 
‎to share their lives together.

00:45:16.163 --> 00:45:19.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Perhaps your mate is an unbeliever.

00:45:19.266 --> 00:45:21.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Differences in belief

00:45:21.368 --> 00:45:23.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎can cause a level of friction,

00:45:23.670 --> 00:45:28.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but how one handles, 
‎or conquers, the situation

00:45:28.041 --> 00:45:32.079 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎can bring you peace 
‎and even be a great witness.

00:45:51.031 --> 00:45:54.535 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎How did 15 years go by so fast?

00:45:57.738 --> 00:46:01.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We were so young when we got married

00:46:01.008 --> 00:46:03.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—maybe too young.

00:46:04.778 --> 00:46:06.980 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We had so little in common.

00:46:20.727 --> 00:46:23.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎When I started studying the Bible,

00:46:23.263 --> 00:46:27.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I thought Thomas would be as excited
‎as I was to learn the truth.

00:46:40.347 --> 00:46:43.016 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But every conversation we had on the subject

00:46:43.016 --> 00:46:46.019 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎seemed to turn into an argument.

00:46:52.826 --> 00:46:57.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Looking back, 
‎I really wish I’d handled it better.

00:46:59.867 --> 00:47:01.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎As the years went by,

00:47:01.869 --> 00:47:05.672 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎he did become more open to discussion.

00:47:21.188 --> 00:47:24.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But it’s been hard worshipping God alone.

00:47:24.224 --> 00:47:28.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Others in the congregation 
‎are able to serve Jehovah together

00:47:28.228 --> 00:47:31.331 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and even reach out for theocratic goals

00:47:31.331 --> 00:47:34.034 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎like the School for Kingdom Evangelizers,

00:47:34.034 --> 00:47:36.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎something I would love to do.

00:47:36.670 --> 00:47:41.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Why can’t I have a husband 
‎who loves Jehovah like I do?

00:47:41.008 --> 00:47:44.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Abigail probably felt the same way

00:47:44.311 --> 00:47:46.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but with more reason.

00:47:51.818 --> 00:47:54.855 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Her husband was a bully and a drunkard

00:47:54.855 --> 00:47:58.158 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and was despised by his entire household.

00:48:17.077 --> 00:48:20.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎At that time, 
‎many marriages were arranged,

00:48:20.213 --> 00:48:24.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎so Abigail had very little control
‎over her circumstances.

00:48:26.119 --> 00:48:28.121 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But her words and actions

00:48:28.121 --> 00:48:30.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎showed that she was a spiritual woman

00:48:30.123 --> 00:48:32.726 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎who didn’t focus 
‎on what she could not control

00:48:32.726 --> 00:48:35.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but on what she could.

00:48:35.529 --> 00:48:38.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I determined to do the same.

00:48:38.065 --> 00:48:42.436 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I meditated on Jesus’ words
‎at Matthew 19:6:

00:48:42.436 --> 00:48:47.374 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“What God has yoked together,
‎let no man put apart.”

00:48:48.275 --> 00:48:51.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎To Jehovah, marriage is permanent

00:48:51.878 --> 00:48:54.214 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—even my marriage to an unbeliever.

00:48:54.214 --> 00:48:58.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So instead of dwelling on changing
‎my husband or my marriage,

00:48:58.085 --> 00:49:00.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I focused on changing myself.

00:49:01.455 --> 00:49:03.557 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Thomas does not love Jehovah,

00:49:03.557 --> 00:49:06.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but he’s not a “Nabal” either.

00:49:06.259 --> 00:49:09.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎He is loyal, and he loves me.

00:49:09.162 --> 00:49:13.000 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎He is entitled to the respect that the Bible 
‎commands wives to show to their husbands.

00:49:13.000 --> 00:49:17.838 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So I’m making an effort 
‎to be more respectful and loving to him.

00:49:17.838 --> 00:49:22.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Thomas hasn’t developed an interest
‎in the truth or started studying. 

00:49:22.576 --> 00:49:27.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But I have the satisfaction of knowing
‎my God is pleased with me,

00:49:27.314 --> 00:49:31.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and I have the same view
‎of marriage that he does.

00:49:53.540 --> 00:49:55.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎How exciting!

00:49:55.542 --> 00:50:00.147 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Is Thomas slowly noticing
‎the benefits of the truth? 

00:50:00.147 --> 00:50:03.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎No doubt, 
‎Emma’s faithful and respectful conduct

00:50:03.950 --> 00:50:08.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎has had a deep impact 
‎on how he views Jehovah.

00:50:08.622 --> 00:50:12.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And the truth can really change a person. 

00:50:12.392 --> 00:50:15.195 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Getting to know Jehovah can help someone

00:50:15.195 --> 00:50:18.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎to get their life back on track.

00:50:18.265 --> 00:50:20.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Two fleshly brothers,

00:50:20.267 --> 00:50:23.870 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Dimitris and Agis Sotiropoulos,

00:50:23.870 --> 00:50:27.941 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎are good examples of how 
‎the good can conquer the evil

00:50:27.941 --> 00:50:31.111 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎despite a challenging upbringing.

00:50:36.950 --> 00:50:39.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎My father was a self-made factory owner.

00:50:39.953 --> 00:50:43.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎He started a business working
‎with rubber and plastics,

00:50:43.957 --> 00:50:48.829 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and we led a financially comfortable way of life.

00:50:48.829 --> 00:50:52.299 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎But in the middle of the 1970’s,

00:50:52.299 --> 00:50:54.701 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎things started going badly with his work.

00:50:54.701 --> 00:50:56.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎For this reason,

00:50:56.703 --> 00:50:59.139 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎he fell into a depression, 
‎and he committed suicide.

00:50:59.139 --> 00:51:01.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎This was a great shock.

00:51:04.377 --> 00:51:06.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I went to the wall and wrote the words

00:51:06.813 --> 00:51:08.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎“He lives.” 

00:51:08.882 --> 00:51:12.819 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I didn’t want to believe that from that day on,

00:51:12.819 --> 00:51:14.988 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I wouldn’t see my father again.

00:51:18.225 --> 00:51:20.861 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎At the age of about ten, I began to develop

00:51:20.861 --> 00:51:23.697 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎strong antireligious tendencies.

00:51:23.697 --> 00:51:26.900 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And later, at the age of 17,

00:51:26.900 --> 00:51:29.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I also expressed them by participating

00:51:29.936 --> 00:51:31.938 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎in the most important incident

00:51:31.938 --> 00:51:35.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎of the student movement 
‎against the military junta

00:51:35.108 --> 00:51:39.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that was prevailing in Greece
‎and ruling the country. 

00:51:39.279 --> 00:51:44.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I became a member of the Communist Party.

00:51:44.117 --> 00:51:46.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I went to Santorini and started a business.

00:51:46.920 --> 00:51:49.089 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I opened a bar.

00:51:49.089 --> 00:51:52.359 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Of course, all this included unsavory things

00:51:52.359 --> 00:51:55.529 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎like immorality, drugs,

00:51:55.529 --> 00:51:58.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and plenty of alcohol.

00:51:58.732 --> 00:52:01.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎A few months later, 
‎I left to study in Germany.

00:52:02.469 --> 00:52:05.605 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It was the first time I met 
‎a brother engaging in street work.

00:52:05.605 --> 00:52:07.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎People would approach him,

00:52:07.707 --> 00:52:09.776 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and some would swear;
‎some even spat at him. 

00:52:09.776 --> 00:52:12.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It impressed me immensely

00:52:12.445 --> 00:52:15.782 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎how he stood calmly 
‎and accepted this treatment.

00:52:15.782 --> 00:52:18.618 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We had interesting conversations.

00:52:18.618 --> 00:52:21.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎My studies ended, and I returned to Greece

00:52:21.454 --> 00:52:24.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎to take on the responsibility of the factory.

00:52:24.558 --> 00:52:27.327 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎When I finished my studies in Germany,

00:52:27.327 --> 00:52:30.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I left with a sense of deep respect

00:52:30.130 --> 00:52:33.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎for Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:52:33.400 --> 00:52:36.469 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The influence of my friends

00:52:36.469 --> 00:52:39.472 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎led me to go into the military,

00:52:39.472 --> 00:52:42.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and there I saw a huge amount of corruption.

00:52:42.976 --> 00:52:45.345 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The hope I had that we humans

00:52:45.345 --> 00:52:48.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎would be able to succeed
‎without external help 

00:52:48.081 --> 00:52:50.083 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—without God—
‎began to collapse,

00:52:50.851 --> 00:52:52.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and then the things I had heard

00:52:52.853 --> 00:52:56.089 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎from Jehovah’s Witnesses
‎suddenly came to my mind.

00:52:57.991 --> 00:53:01.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The same afternoon, 
‎I sought out a family friend,

00:53:01.828 --> 00:53:04.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the mother of a childhood friend, named Lily.

00:53:04.798 --> 00:53:07.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I said to her, “Please give me a Bible

00:53:07.500 --> 00:53:11.204 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and some Bible study publications
‎because I want to study them.” 

00:53:11.204 --> 00:53:13.206 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I read everywhere,

00:53:13.206 --> 00:53:15.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and anything that I didn’t understand,

00:53:15.542 --> 00:53:17.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I wrote down in a notebook.

00:53:17.777 --> 00:53:20.714 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I got to the point, in just a few days,

00:53:20.714 --> 00:53:23.817 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎where I had written down 80 to 90 questions.

00:53:23.817 --> 00:53:25.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Harry impressed me

00:53:25.986 --> 00:53:28.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎because every time I asked him a question,

00:53:28.688 --> 00:53:31.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎he gave me the answer from the Bible.

00:53:31.024 --> 00:53:34.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎That convinced me that I’d found the truth.

00:53:34.561 --> 00:53:36.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎So in that moment,

00:53:36.730 --> 00:53:41.167 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I decided to leave the military 
‎and to quit smoking.

00:53:41.167 --> 00:53:43.737 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎A few months passed by,

00:53:43.737 --> 00:53:46.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎where I was occupied mostly with the factory,

00:53:46.172 --> 00:53:48.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎until I recognized

00:53:48.541 --> 00:53:52.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that for me to make progress in the truth,

00:53:52.078 --> 00:53:54.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I had to sell my shares in the factory. 

00:53:55.815 --> 00:53:59.019 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And on July 7, 1984, I was baptized.

00:53:59.019 --> 00:54:02.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The authorities
‎—the police, the mayor,

00:54:02.923 --> 00:54:05.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the health inspectors—
‎began to demand money

00:54:05.392 --> 00:54:08.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎so that I could keep the bar open.

00:54:11.097 --> 00:54:13.767 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I refused all the things they asked of me,

00:54:13.767 --> 00:54:16.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and so the war became harder

00:54:17.704 --> 00:54:22.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎until one night when I went 
‎to open the door to enter my home;

00:54:22.108 --> 00:54:24.711 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I heard a tramping from behind,

00:54:24.711 --> 00:54:27.881 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I tried to turn and see,
‎and as I turned,

00:54:27.881 --> 00:54:29.883 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I was hit in the face.

00:54:29.883 --> 00:54:31.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎During that time,

00:54:31.885 --> 00:54:34.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎when all of this was happening,
‎my brother Dimitris arrived.

00:54:39.059 --> 00:54:42.362 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎As brothers, 
‎we never really had a relationship.

00:54:42.362 --> 00:54:45.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎When he came to Santorini
‎and began to talk to me

00:54:45.465 --> 00:54:48.468 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and help me understand 
‎what was happening to me,

00:54:48.468 --> 00:54:53.106 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I realized that this was a different Dimitris.

00:54:53.106 --> 00:54:56.543 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I said to him, “I want us 
‎to start studying the Bible together.” 

00:54:56.543 --> 00:54:59.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I had the Bible with me 
‎almost everywhere I went

00:54:59.412 --> 00:55:01.481 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎so that I could read it. 

00:55:01.481 --> 00:55:06.319 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I realized that Jehovah was helping me 
‎to understand what I was living for. 

00:55:06.319 --> 00:55:08.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎He was helping me to understand

00:55:08.621 --> 00:55:11.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that I could have a real goal, a purpose,

00:55:11.891 --> 00:55:14.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and a hope.

00:55:14.394 --> 00:55:18.598 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎On the day of my baptism,
‎I felt that I was drawing closer to Jehovah.

00:55:19.599 --> 00:55:23.103 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I felt like my smile went from ear to ear.

00:55:24.504 --> 00:55:26.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And now with Lydia,

00:55:26.506 --> 00:55:28.742 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎I have the great joy of serving

00:55:28.742 --> 00:55:31.911 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎in the Romany territory.

00:55:31.911 --> 00:55:34.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We enjoy very nice Bible studies.

00:55:34.914 --> 00:55:36.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It is truly something

00:55:36.950 --> 00:55:39.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that shows you Jehovah’s love,

00:55:39.285 --> 00:55:42.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎interest, and affection

00:55:42.122 --> 00:55:44.124 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—things that I had felt

00:55:44.124 --> 00:55:46.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎many years ago 
‎when I studied with my brother.

00:55:46.626 --> 00:55:50.196 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Today, my brother and I 
‎love each other very much.

00:55:50.196 --> 00:55:53.833 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎It is a relationship characterized

00:55:53.833 --> 00:55:56.169 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎by brotherly love

00:55:56.169 --> 00:55:59.539 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎as it is expressed in the Bible.

00:55:59.539 --> 00:56:01.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎We are very close to each other.

00:56:01.841 --> 00:56:04.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎This is really a change.

00:56:04.611 --> 00:56:08.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Now we are truly brothers!

00:56:10.784 --> 00:56:15.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Today, both Dimitris 
‎and Agis serve as elders

00:56:15.488 --> 00:56:18.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and have spent many years
‎in the full-time ministry.

00:56:18.758 --> 00:56:20.827 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Have you noticed the many ways

00:56:20.827 --> 00:56:24.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎we have seen the good conquer 
‎the evil in this month’s broadcast?

00:56:24.464 --> 00:56:26.800 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Our brothers in Korea

00:56:26.800 --> 00:56:29.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎were able to endure unjust imprisonment

00:56:29.869 --> 00:56:32.338 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎with the support of their fellow believers.

00:56:33.740 --> 00:56:36.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Viktor Winter, 
‎who was also imprisoned,

00:56:36.242 --> 00:56:38.211 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎conquered the evil

00:56:38.211 --> 00:56:40.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎by maintaining a theocratic routine.

00:56:41.581 --> 00:56:44.050 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Our music video helped us appreciate

00:56:44.050 --> 00:56:46.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the value of our true friends
‎in the congregation,

00:56:46.686 --> 00:56:50.690 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎who will help us fulfill our ministry
‎in this wicked world. 

00:56:51.891 --> 00:56:54.094 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Also, Brother Jackson

00:56:54.094 --> 00:56:57.363 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎shared principles to help us
‎overcome negative feelings

00:56:57.363 --> 00:57:01.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎we may have about others
‎as a result of our imperfection.

00:57:02.569 --> 00:57:06.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Over time, 
‎Emma learned to apply those principles

00:57:06.039 --> 00:57:08.842 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎in dealing 
‎with her unbelieving husband, Thomas.

00:57:09.509 --> 00:57:12.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎And finally, 
‎the truth conquered the evil

00:57:12.712 --> 00:57:16.583 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎when the Sotiropoulos brothers
‎were able to clean up their lives.

00:57:17.450 --> 00:57:21.254 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Before we conclude,
‎we have an announcement to make.

00:57:21.254 --> 00:57:23.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎You will be happy to know

00:57:23.289 --> 00:57:27.560 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎that the next installment 
‎of the video series Was it Designed?

00:57:27.560 --> 00:57:30.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎entitled The Seahorse’s Tail

00:57:30.263 --> 00:57:32.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎is available on Video on Demand

00:57:32.799 --> 00:57:37.170 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and jw.org starting this month.

00:57:37.170 --> 00:57:40.673 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Perhaps you can watch it 
‎during your next Family Worship evening.

00:57:41.908 --> 00:57:44.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Let’s also briefly visit 
‎our brothers and sisters in Portugal.

00:57:46.246 --> 00:57:49.616 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎As the most western country
‎in continental Europe,

00:57:49.616 --> 00:57:52.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Portugal is known 
‎as the place where the land ends

00:57:52.986 --> 00:57:55.188 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and the sea begins.

00:57:55.188 --> 00:57:58.758 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Mainland Portugal 
‎has over 800 kilometers,

00:57:58.758 --> 00:58:01.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎or over 500 miles, of Atlantic Coast.

00:58:03.229 --> 00:58:05.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎In the southern part of the country,

00:58:05.231 --> 00:58:09.135 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎they have over 3,000 hours
‎of sunshine per year. 

00:58:10.403 --> 00:58:12.539 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Portugal became world renowned

00:58:12.539 --> 00:58:16.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎as a seafaring nation 
‎with colonies around the world.

00:58:18.044 --> 00:58:20.980 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎In the 15th century,
‎navigators and explorers

00:58:20.980 --> 00:58:23.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎from Portugal
‎traveled to distant places

00:58:23.383 --> 00:58:27.220 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎such as Brazil, India, 
‎and many parts of Africa.

00:58:28.488 --> 00:58:32.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The good news reached Portugal in 1925,

00:58:32.392 --> 00:58:34.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎but the work was either restricted

00:58:34.394 --> 00:58:39.399 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎or under ban from 1926 to 1974. 

00:58:41.334 --> 00:58:43.903 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎However, the brothers 
‎and sisters were good examples

00:58:43.903 --> 00:58:47.207 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎of “conquering the evil with the good.”

00:58:47.207 --> 00:58:50.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Despite the restrictions and persecution,

00:58:50.476 --> 00:58:52.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎they continued to preach

00:58:52.812 --> 00:58:55.615 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and gather together to worship Jehovah.

00:58:56.883 --> 00:59:01.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎When the Witnesses 
‎gained legal recognition in 1974,

00:59:01.321 --> 00:59:06.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎the country reported
‎about 13,500 publishers

00:59:06.059 --> 00:59:10.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and almost 40,000 attended
‎the first public meeting. 

00:59:10.797 --> 00:59:15.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Today, the country reports
‎some 49,500 publishers

00:59:15.802 --> 00:59:20.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and a ratio of 1 publisher 
‎to about 200 people

00:59:20.807 --> 00:59:23.276 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎—one of the lowest ratios in Europe.

00:59:24.410 --> 00:59:26.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎The ratio is even lower in Almada,

00:59:26.546 --> 00:59:30.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎which is across the Tagus River
‎from the capital city, Lisbon. 

00:59:30.350 --> 00:59:33.753 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎In Almada, there are 16 congregations

00:59:33.753 --> 00:59:36.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎with almost 1,400 publishers in total

00:59:36.923 --> 00:59:40.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎with a ratio of 1 publisher
‎to about 100 residents. 

00:59:41.861 --> 00:59:45.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎Many of the brothers and sisters
‎in Almada are older

00:59:45.298 --> 00:59:48.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎and endured faithfully during the ban,

00:59:48.101 --> 00:59:50.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎setting an example to the younger ones.

00:59:52.438 --> 00:59:54.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎In addition to theocratic activities,

00:59:54.540 --> 00:59:58.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎our brothers in Almada 
‎regularly come together to associate,

00:59:58.678 --> 01:00:02.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎which can include 
‎a game of soccer or singing songs.

01:00:10.089 --> 01:00:13.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎They all send their love and greetings

01:00:13.059 --> 01:00:16.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎to the worldwide brotherhood.

01:00:16.062 --> 01:00:19.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎This is JW Broadcasting

01:00:19.365 --> 01:00:23.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‎from the world headquarters
‎of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

